1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:07,079
This is Party Quips, the web party game for people who think board game night needs fewer tiny plastic pieces and way more bad decisions.

2
00:00:07,079 --> 00:00:12,788
Open it on the TV, pick a game, and everybody joins from their phone with a room code or QR code.

3
00:00:12,788 --> 00:00:13,930
No download.

4
00:00:13,930 --> 00:00:14,963
No account.

5
00:00:14,963 --> 00:00:17,764
No group chat full of setup instructions.

6
00:00:17,764 --> 00:00:19,580
Start with Witty Quips.

7
00:00:19,580 --> 00:00:28,701
The TV throws out ridiculous prompts, players type their best answers, and then everyone votes for the response that deserves applause, concern, or both.

8
00:00:28,701 --> 00:00:29,939
Somebody stuck?

9
00:00:29,939 --> 00:00:39,110
Party Quips can auto-generate a quip, which is very helpful when your friend says, "I am funny under pressure," and then types three dots for thirty seconds.

10
00:00:39,110 --> 00:00:44,591
Then there is Fib Finder, where players write fake answers to weird facts and try to fool the room.

11
00:00:44,591 --> 00:00:50,110
It is trivia, lying, and confidence in one suspicious little package.

12
00:00:50,110 --> 00:00:54,158
Deadly Trivia keeps the pressure on with fast multiple-choice rounds.

13
00:00:54,158 --> 00:00:55,961
Get it right, stay alive.

14
00:00:55,961 --> 00:01:00,300
Get it wrong, and the TV starts looking at you like it knows what you did.

15
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:10,060
The host screen keeps the whole room moving with timers, QR codes, player lists, scoreboards, voting screens, and results that are big enough for the couch to yell at.

16
00:01:10,060 --> 00:01:14,050
Phone screens stay simple: join, answer, vote, survive.

17
00:01:14,050 --> 00:01:16,802
Your friends do not need to learn a rulebook.

18
00:01:16,802 --> 00:01:19,747
They just need thumbs and questionable instincts.

19
00:01:19,747 --> 00:01:27,944
There is also feedback reporting built in, because every great party app needs a way to say, "This broke," before someone blames the Wi-Fi.

20
00:01:27,944 --> 00:01:38,088
Party Quips runs in the browser, works great on TV and phones, supports multiple game modes, and now has a much bigger prompt pool, so the jokes can keep making terrible choices all night.

21
00:01:38,088 --> 00:01:46,959
Grab some friends, put it on the big screen, and find out who is clever, who is convincing, and who should absolutely never be trusted with a fake historical fact.

